279
00:11:52,178 --> 00:11:54,545
Whoa!

280
00:11:54,545 --> 00:11:54,646


281
00:11:54,647 --> 00:11:57,412
- Hello, Chambers.
- Hello, sir.

282
00:11:57,412 --> 00:11:57,517


283
00:11:57,517 --> 00:12:00,043
- Hello, Inspector.
- What's the trouble? Anything wrong?

284
00:12:00,043 --> 00:12:00,153


285
00:12:00,153 --> 00:12:02,918
Indian raid. Four of my workmen wounded.
And they've stolen 2O head of horses.

286
00:12:02,918 --> 00:12:03,021


287
00:12:03,022 --> 00:12:06,424
If we hadn't caught them in time,
they'd have cleaned out the whole corral.

288
00:12:06,424 --> 00:12:06,526


289
00:12:06,526 --> 00:12:08,494
- Inspector, turn out 1 O men.
- Yes, sir.

290
00:12:08,494 --> 00:12:08,594


291
00:12:08,595 --> 00:12:10,586
- Mr. Randall, you'll take out the patrol.
- Sir.

292
00:12:10,586 --> 00:12:10,697


293
00:12:10,697 --> 00:12:13,096
- Go to the construction camp and
track down the raiders. - Yes, sir.

294
00:12:13,097 --> 00:12:13,199


295
00:12:13,199 --> 00:12:17,295
- I'll need your doctor too.
- Then come inside. We'll get him.

296
00:12:17,295 --> 00:12:17,403


297
00:12:17,403 --> 00:12:20,600
- Call <i>the doctor.</i>
- <i>[ Vicky] Harlan!</i>

298
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:20,706


299
00:12:20,707 --> 00:12:23,140
Why, Vicky, what on earth
are you doing here?

300
00:12:23,141 --> 00:12:23,242


301
00:12:23,243 --> 00:12:27,111
- Came out for a visit. - Well, why
didn't you let me know you were coming?

302
00:12:27,111 --> 00:12:27,213


303
00:12:27,213 --> 00:12:29,181
I didn't even let Dad
know I was coming, did I?

304
00:12:29,181 --> 00:12:29,281


305
00:12:29,282 --> 00:12:32,274
[Chuckles] No. As a matter of fact,
she didn't. Oh, Doctor.

306
00:12:32,274 --> 00:12:32,385


307
00:12:32,385 --> 00:12:34,353
- Yes, sir.
- Go back to camp with Mr. Chambers.

308
00:12:34,353 --> 00:12:34,453


309
00:12:34,454 --> 00:12:36,445
- You're needed there.
- I'll get my kit, sir.

310
00:12:36,445 --> 00:12:36,556


311
00:12:36,556 --> 00:12:39,355
- Mr. Churchill, check the guard.
Prepare for any emergency. - Yes, sir.

312
00:12:39,355 --> 00:12:39,459


313
00:12:39,459 --> 00:12:42,427
- You may be able to assist him, Mr. Williams?
- Yes, sir.

314
00:12:42,428 --> 00:12:42,528


315
00:12:42,528 --> 00:12:45,122
- Good night, Miss Standing.
- Good night. Anything serious, Dad?

316
00:12:45,123 --> 00:12:45,230


317
00:12:45,231 --> 00:12:47,461
- Good night.
-just a little Indian trouble at my camp.

318
00:12:47,461 --> 00:12:47,567


319
00:12:47,567 --> 00:12:49,797
- Nothing for you to worry about.
- It's hardly the best time...

320
00:12:49,797 --> 00:12:49,901


321
00:12:49,902 --> 00:12:53,202
For you to have come out here, but I can't
tell you how pleased I am to see you.

322
00:12:53,202 --> 00:12:53,306


323
00:12:53,306 --> 00:12:56,332
- Don't tell me I leave you speechless, Harlan.
- [Chuckles]

324
00:12:56,332 --> 00:12:56,442


325
00:12:56,442 --> 00:12:59,844
You always did. Superintendent,
why didn't you give me notice?

326
00:12:59,844 --> 00:12:59,946


327
00:12:59,946 --> 00:13:02,278
I'd have met her at Winnipeg
and brought her out here on a special.

328
00:13:02,278 --> 00:13:02,381


329
00:13:02,382 --> 00:13:04,612
You didn't give
the Canadian Pacific a chance.

330
00:13:04,612 --> 00:13:04,716


331
00:13:04,717 --> 00:13:06,685
We'll see what can be done
about that in the future.

332
00:13:06,686 --> 00:13:06,786


333
00:13:06,786 --> 00:13:09,778
- You bet we will.
- The patrol's ready, Mr. Chambers.

334
00:13:09,778 --> 00:13:09,889


335
00:13:09,889 --> 00:13:14,122
Thank you. I'll be back for a real visit as soon
we've settled with these horse thieves.

336
00:13:14,122 --> 00:13:14,227


337
00:13:14,227 --> 00:13:16,286
- Good night.
- Good night and good luck.

338
00:13:16,286 --> 00:13:16,395


339
00:13:16,396 --> 00:13:18,865
Thanks. We need it.
Thank you, Superintendent.

340
00:13:18,865 --> 00:13:18,965


341
00:13:18,965 --> 00:13:21,330
- Not at all. Good night.
- Good night.

342
00:13:21,331 --> 00:13:21,434


343
00:13:21,434 --> 00:13:23,664
- [ Chattering]
- [Shouts Command, indistinct]

344
00:13:23,664 --> 00:13:23,770


345
00:13:23,770 --> 00:13:25,795
<i>[ Dogs Barking]</i>

346
00:13:25,795 --> 00:13:29,475


347
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:33,207
Probably the same band that
attacked the wagon train, sir.

348
00:13:33,207 --> 00:13:33,312


349
00:13:33,313 --> 00:13:37,147
This will give the rail road people another
opportunity to clamor for government troops.

350
00:13:37,147 --> 00:13:37,250


351
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:39,412
I hope not, sir.

352
00:13:39,412 --> 00:13:39,519


353
00:13:39,519 --> 00:13:43,181
We'll try a direct hit.
I wanna get Big Eagle in here for a talk.

354
00:13:43,182 --> 00:13:43,289


355
00:13:43,289 --> 00:13:45,348
It's only a three-hour ride
to his camp.

356
00:13:45,349 --> 00:13:45,458


357
00:13:45,458 --> 00:13:47,859
- If you like, I'll have him here in the morning.
- Good.

358
00:13:47,859 --> 00:13:47,959


359
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:49,985
- Good night, sir.
- Good night.

360
00:13:49,986 --> 00:14:11,783


361
00:14:11,784 --> 00:14:14,116
<i>G,' [Continues]</i>

362
00:14:14,117 --> 00:14:16,723


363
00:14:16,723 --> 00:14:18,782
JM Ends]

364
00:14:18,782 --> 00:14:24,530


365
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:26,521
<i>[ Door Opens ]</i>

366
00:14:26,521 --> 00:14:26,632


367
00:14:26,632 --> 00:14:30,796
Good mornin'.
You're up mighty early.

368
00:14:30,797 --> 00:14:30,902


369
00:14:30,903 --> 00:14:34,032
- Mr. Monty hasn't come home yet, has he?
- He has not.

370
00:14:34,032 --> 00:14:34,140


371
00:14:34,140 --> 00:14:36,232
- Where did he go?
- On duty.

372
00:14:36,233 --> 00:14:36,342


373
00:14:36,342 --> 00:14:38,868
- Where else would he be goin'?
- When will he get back?

374
00:14:38,868 --> 00:14:38,978


375
00:14:38,978 --> 00:14:41,743
I not be knowin' that.

376
00:14:41,743 --> 00:14:41,848


377
00:14:41,848 --> 00:14:44,374
- What areyou making?
- Never mind now. Never mind.

378
00:14:44,374 --> 00:14:44,484


379
00:14:44,484 --> 00:14:46,748
Curiosity killed
the cat, you know.

380
00:14:46,748 --> 00:14:46,853


381
00:14:46,853 --> 00:14:50,289
You shouldn't be sewing.
That's a woman's work.

382
00:14:50,289 --> 00:14:50,390


383
00:14:50,390 --> 00:14:52,950
Not in the army, darlin'.
That's where I learned it.

384
00:14:52,950 --> 00:14:53,059


385
00:14:53,059 --> 00:14:55,619
You men on the fort should have wives
to do things for you.

386
00:14:55,619 --> 00:14:55,728


387
00:14:55,728 --> 00:14:57,719
Wives, is it?
[Laughs]

388
00:14:57,719 --> 00:14:57,830


389
00:14:57,830 --> 00:15:00,458
Heaven pity the poor girl
that'd marry a man in this outfit.

390
00:15:00,459 --> 00:15:00,565


391
00:15:00,566 --> 00:15:04,969
- Why?
- 'Tis a no-good lot of heartbreakers, they are.

392
00:15:04,970 --> 00:15:05,071


393
00:15:05,071 --> 00:15:09,235
- Are you a heartbreaker?
- Well, I've had me day.

394
00:15:09,235 --> 00:15:09,342


395
00:15:09,342 --> 00:15:13,506
Of course, I did have certain
disadvantages in the way of a face, but-

396
00:15:13,506 --> 00:15:13,613


397
00:15:13,613 --> 00:15:15,604
Hold your hush now.

398
00:15:15,604 --> 00:15:15,715


399
00:15:15,715 --> 00:15:18,810
Stop your questions
till I get this last button sewed on.

400
00:15:18,810 --> 00:15:18,918


401
00:15:18,918 --> 00:15:22,081
- Is Mr. Monty a heartbreaker too?
- isn't he, though?

402
00:15:22,081 --> 00:15:22,188


403
00:15:22,188 --> 00:15:25,624
You oughta seen him at Regina
when he was there. [ Laughs]

404
00:15:25,624 --> 00:15:25,725


405
00:15:25,725 --> 00:15:29,684
Who was he talking about last night
when he said she was so beautiful?

406
00:15:29,684 --> 00:15:29,795


407
00:15:29,796 --> 00:15:33,788
- And who'd be askin'?
- Oh, I was just wondering.

408
00:15:33,789 --> 00:15:33,900


409
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:35,868
You know very well
who he was talking about.

410
00:15:35,868 --> 00:15:35,968


411
00:15:35,968 --> 00:15:38,369
But don't you bother.
She'll be goin' home soon.

412
00:15:38,369 --> 00:15:38,471


413
00:15:38,471 --> 00:15:41,372
We'll have Mr. Monty
all to ourselves. [ Laughs]

414
00:15:41,372 --> 00:15:41,474


415
00:15:41,474 --> 00:15:44,772
There.
It's finished.

416
00:15:44,773 --> 00:15:44,877


417
00:15:44,877 --> 00:15:47,505
- And I hope it fits ya.
- Is it for me?

418
00:15:47,506 --> 00:15:47,612


419
00:15:47,613 --> 00:15:49,604
And who else would I
be sewin' for all this night?

420
00:15:49,604 --> 00:15:49,715


421
00:15:49,715 --> 00:15:52,047
And there's these
to go with it.

422
00:15:52,048 --> 00:15:52,151


423
00:15:52,151 --> 00:15:54,779
- I be makin' ya other things
when I get around to it. - Oh!

424
00:15:54,779 --> 00:15:54,887


425
00:15:54,887 --> 00:15:58,346
[Laughing] Now I'm goin' to the mess hall
to get you some breakfast.

426
00:15:58,346 --> 00:15:58,457


427
00:15:58,458 --> 00:16:00,449
Thank you, Mr. Pat!
Thank you!

428
00:16:00,449 --> 00:16:00,560


429
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:04,017
That's all right, darlin'.
That's all right.

430
00:16:04,018 --> 00:16:13,973


431
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:15,964
What are those Indians
coming here for?

432
00:16:15,964 --> 00:16:16,075


433
00:16:16,075 --> 00:16:18,407
Don't worry. They won't hurt you
while you're with us.

434
00:16:18,408 --> 00:16:18,511


435
00:16:18,511 --> 00:16:21,173
- Mr. Monty's bringin' 'em in for a powwow.
- Oh.

436
00:16:21,173 --> 00:16:21,280


437
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:23,874
Come along now.

438
00:16:23,874 --> 00:16:23,983


439
00:16:23,983 --> 00:16:25,974
He looks all right though,
doesn't he?

440
00:16:25,974 --> 00:16:26,085


441
00:16:26,085 --> 00:16:28,952
Of course he's all right.
Come on. Inside with ya.

442
00:16:28,952 --> 00:16:31,123


443
00:16:31,123 --> 00:16:34,855
<i>[Standing] “The sun has shone on us many
days in peace, my brothers.</i>

444
00:16:34,855 --> 00:16:34,960


445
00:16:34,961 --> 00:16:38,259
<i>Now a cloud
passes over the sun.</i>

446
00:16:38,260 --> 00:16:38,364


447
00:16:38,364 --> 00:16:42,323
<i>Two days ago,
a wagon train was destroyed.</i>

448
00:16:42,324 --> 00:16:42,435


449
00:16:42,435 --> 00:16:48,067
Last night, the Iron Horse camp
was attacked and many horses stolen.“

450
00:16:48,067 --> 00:16:49,542


451
00:16:49,542 --> 00:16:53,069
Indians who kill wagon train
steal horses...

452
00:16:53,069 --> 00:16:53,179


453
00:16:53,179 --> 00:16:55,170
Not from camp of Big Eagle.

454
00:16:55,170 --> 00:16:55,281


455
00:16:55,281 --> 00:16:57,716
They were Blackfeet.
But if you mean, Wolf Pelt...

456
00:16:57,716 --> 00:16:57,817


457
00:16:57,817 --> 00:17:00,013
That they were from
some other part of your tribe...

458
00:17:00,013 --> 00:17:00,119


459
00:17:00,119 --> 00:17:03,282
<i>That does not lessen
the responsibility of your chief</i>

460
00:17:03,282 --> 00:17:03,389


461
00:17:03,389 --> 00:17:06,689
If Blackfeet Indian
make trouble...

462
00:17:06,689 --> 00:17:06,791


463
00:17:06,792 --> 00:17:10,888
We'll send guilty ones
to white chief.

464
00:17:10,888 --> 00:17:10,996


465
00:17:10,997 --> 00:17:13,692
- I'll hold you to that.
- Give word.

466
00:17:13,693 --> 00:17:13,799


467
00:17:13,799 --> 00:17:15,927
I believe that, Big Eagle.

468
00:17:15,927 --> 00:17:16,035


469
00:17:16,035 --> 00:17:20,199
And I'm willing to admit that these raids
may have occurred without your knowledge.

470
00:17:20,199 --> 00:17:20,306


471
00:17:20,306 --> 00:17:23,765
But so that we shall have
a clear understanding in the future...

472
00:17:23,765 --> 00:17:23,876


473
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:28,040
I have prepared a paper,
a fair and honorable bond...

474
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:28,147


475
00:17:28,147 --> 00:17:30,172
Between the white
and the red man.

476
00:17:30,172 --> 00:17:33,752


477
00:17:33,753 --> 00:17:36,448
We'll speak in council
with my chiefs.

478
00:17:36,449 --> 00:17:36,555


479
00:17:36,556 --> 00:17:39,956
And I'll expect your answer
within five days.

480
00:17:39,957 --> 00:17:40,059


481
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:42,426
In the meantime,
I'll need some guarantee...

482
00:17:42,426 --> 00:17:42,527


483
00:17:42,528 --> 00:17:44,656
<i>That you'll keep
your warriors in check.</i>

484
00:17:44,656 --> 00:17:44,764


485
00:17:44,764 --> 00:17:46,755
Huh?

486
00:17:46,755 --> 00:17:46,866


487
00:17:46,866 --> 00:17:51,394
The white chief means he has great
responsibility to the queen mother.

488
00:17:51,394 --> 00:17:51,504


489
00:17:51,504 --> 00:17:53,472
He must have some token-

490
00:17:53,472 --> 00:17:53,572


491
00:17:53,573 --> 00:17:56,599
The guns ofyouryoung braves
or your running horses-

492
00:17:56,599 --> 00:17:56,709


493
00:17:56,709 --> 00:17:59,371
To prove that you'll
keep your promise.

494
00:17:59,371 --> 00:18:00,713


495
00:18:00,713 --> 00:18:02,738
Huh.

496
00:18:02,738 --> 00:18:04,717


497
00:18:04,717 --> 00:18:10,349
If white chief think Big Eagle
speak with forked tongue...

498
00:18:10,349 --> 00:18:10,456


499
00:18:10,456 --> 00:18:14,051
Will give something
more close to heart.

500
00:18:14,051 --> 00:18:16,628


501
00:18:16,629 --> 00:18:18,688
Little Chief stay here.

502
00:18:18,688 --> 00:18:18,797


503
00:18:18,798 --> 00:18:22,325
Token Big Eagle's word
is straight.

504
00:18:22,325 --> 00:18:24,570


505
00:18:24,570 --> 00:18:27,096
That's more
than I'd ask for...

506
00:18:27,096 --> 00:18:27,206


507
00:18:27,206 --> 00:18:30,471
But it will do no harm for your son
to learn the ways of the white man.

508
00:18:30,472 --> 00:18:30,575


509
00:18:30,576 --> 00:18:35,412
And you may be sure he'll have the best
treatment that we can offer.

510
00:18:35,412 --> 00:18:36,716


511
00:18:36,716 --> 00:18:40,344
Go now.
Send word soon.

512
00:18:40,345 --> 00:18:47,326


513
00:18:47,326 --> 00:18:50,626
- The Indians are coming out.
- Oh?

514
00:18:50,626 --> 00:18:50,730


515
00:18:50,730 --> 00:18:52,994
What do you suppose
they were doing in there?

516
00:18:52,994 --> 00:18:53,099


517
00:18:53,099 --> 00:18:56,727
Probably gettin' blue blazes from the O.C.
for the devilry they've been up to.

518
00:18:56,728 --> 00:18:58,437


519
00:18:58,437 --> 00:19:01,702
There's something
I'd like to tell them too.

520
00:19:01,703 --> 00:19:01,806


521
00:19:01,807 --> 00:19:05,641
Where ya goin'?
Come back here. Come back here!

522
00:19:05,642 --> 00:19:07,780


523
00:19:07,780 --> 00:19:09,748
[Chattering]

524
00:19:09,748 --> 00:19:09,848


525
00:19:09,849 --> 00:19:11,975
Are you the chieflndian?

526
00:19:11,976 --> 00:19:12,084


527
00:19:12,084 --> 00:19:14,712
Hmm.
Me Big Eagle.

528
00:19:14,713 --> 00:19:14,819


529
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:19,690
Well, I certainly hope Mr. Standing is going
to make you Indians behave from now on.

530
00:19:19,690 --> 00:19:19,792


531
00:19:19,792 --> 00:19:22,989
And if you got what you deserved,
he'd send you all tojail.

532
00:19:22,989 --> 00:19:23,095


533
00:19:23,095 --> 00:19:25,427
That's where you belong for what you've
been doing. What right have you-

534
00:19:25,428 --> 00:19:25,531


535
00:19:25,531 --> 00:19:29,434
Here,just a minute, Sue.
You must forgive her, Big Eagle.

536
00:19:29,434 --> 00:19:29,535


537
00:19:29,535 --> 00:19:32,766
This little girl was the only survivor
of the wagon train.

538
00:19:32,766 --> 00:19:38,177


539
00:19:38,177 --> 00:19:43,047
Golden Hawk,
little spirit of the sun.

540
00:19:43,047 --> 00:19:43,149


541
00:19:43,149 --> 00:19:46,915
Big Eagle sorry
you have trouble.

542
00:19:46,915 --> 00:19:47,019


543
00:19:47,019 --> 00:19:49,078
<i>Will not happen again.</i>

544
00:19:49,079 --> 00:19:49,188


545
00:19:49,188 --> 00:19:51,680
I don't see why you want to fight
the white people anyway.

546
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:51,791


547
00:19:51,791 --> 00:19:55,284
- They haven't done anything to hurt you.
- [Chuckles]

548
00:19:55,284 --> 00:19:55,393


549
00:19:55,394 --> 00:19:58,762
Will send present
to little Golden Hawk.

550
00:19:58,762 --> 00:20:01,200


551
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:04,465
We be good friend now.

552
00:20:04,465 --> 00:20:14,413


553
00:20:14,413 --> 00:20:17,508
<i>[ Dogs Barking]</i>

554
00:20:17,508 --> 00:20:20,753


555
00:20:20,753 --> 00:20:24,246
- Do you really think he's sorry?
- Yes, I'm sure he is.

556
00:20:24,246 --> 00:20:24,355


557
00:20:24,356 --> 00:20:26,324
But where did you
get all this? Mmm!

558
00:20:26,325 --> 00:20:26,425


