00:39:43,081 --> 00:39:45,345
Come on.

1119
00:39:45,345 --> 00:39:50,255


1120
00:39:50,255 --> 00:39:54,817
- [ Sighs]
- What's the matter now?

1121
00:39:54,817 --> 00:39:54,926


1122
00:39:54,926 --> 00:39:57,621
You have a face as long
as the old woman that kissed the cow.

1123
00:39:57,622 --> 00:40:00,931


1124
00:40:00,932 --> 00:40:03,663
- He's in love with her.
- [ Laughing] Me darlin'.

1125
00:40:03,663 --> 00:40:03,767


1126
00:40:03,768 --> 00:40:07,329
'Tis one of the delightful misfortunes
that overtakes the male of the species.

1127
00:40:07,329 --> 00:40:07,438


1128
00:40:07,438 --> 00:40:09,964
'Tis me that knows.
[Laughing]

1129
00:40:09,964 --> 00:40:11,943


1130
00:40:11,943 --> 00:40:14,935
I wish she'd go back
where she came from.

1131
00:40:14,935 --> 00:40:15,046


1132
00:40:15,046 --> 00:40:18,277
Oh-ho.
'Tisjealous, you are.

1133
00:40:18,277 --> 00:40:18,382


1134
00:40:18,383 --> 00:40:21,944
I am not. But she couldn't take care
of him the way we do.

1135
00:40:21,944 --> 00:40:22,053


1136
00:40:22,053 --> 00:40:24,021
I'll bet she couldn't
even make his bed.

1137
00:40:24,021 --> 00:40:24,121


1138
00:40:24,122 --> 00:40:26,784
- And you're not doing it right either.
- I'm not, ain't I?

1139
00:40:26,784 --> 00:40:26,891


1140
00:40:26,891 --> 00:40:29,155
You haven't the covers up
close enough around his neck.

1141
00:40:29,155 --> 00:40:29,260


1142
00:40:29,260 --> 00:40:31,786
- Oh. Huh.
- And you should unfold his nightshirt...

1143
00:40:31,786 --> 00:40:31,896


1144
00:40:31,896 --> 00:40:33,864
And have it
all laid out for him.

1145
00:40:33,864 --> 00:40:33,964


1146
00:40:33,965 --> 00:40:37,993
What are you tryin' to do, spoil him?
Here, me bucko, I'll take that.

1147
00:40:37,993 --> 00:40:42,774


1148
00:40:42,774 --> 00:40:47,642
Oh, Mr. Pat! And I taught him
how to dance with her.

1149
00:40:47,643 --> 00:40:47,745


1150
00:40:47,745 --> 00:40:51,113
Heaven help us.

1151
00:40:51,113 --> 00:40:51,215


1152
00:40:51,215 --> 00:40:54,014
I know, I know.

1153
00:40:54,014 --> 00:40:54,118


1154
00:40:54,118 --> 00:40:57,110
'Tis a terrible thing
to be a woman in love.

1155
00:40:57,111 --> 00:40:57,220


1156
00:40:57,221 --> 00:41:00,623
- Oh, Mr. Pat!
- Ah, yes, I understand.

1157
00:41:00,623 --> 00:41:00,725


1158
00:41:00,725 --> 00:41:03,456
Neveryou mind.
Neveryou mind now.

1159
00:41:03,456 --> 00:41:03,560


1160
00:41:03,561 --> 00:41:06,030
And it's
a heartbreaking ruffian he is.

1161
00:41:06,030 --> 00:41:06,130


1162
00:41:06,130 --> 00:41:10,465
He is not a ruffian.
I won't let you say that.

1163
00:41:10,465 --> 00:41:10,568


1164
00:41:10,568 --> 00:41:14,334
Oh, well, have it
your own way, me darlin'.

1165
00:41:14,334 --> 00:41:14,438


1166
00:41:14,439 --> 00:41:16,531
Have it your own way.

1167
00:41:16,532 --> 00:41:16,641


1168
00:41:16,641 --> 00:41:20,168
Close them pretty eyes now.

1169
00:41:20,168 --> 00:41:20,278


1170
00:41:20,278 --> 00:41:24,738
<i>♪♪</i> [ <i>Singing</i> 1

1171
00:41:24,738 --> 00:41:34,192


1172
00:41:34,192 --> 00:41:34,359
Good night, Miss Standing.
It's thejoiliest night we've ever had.

1173
00:41:34,359 --> 00:41:36,883
Good night, Miss Standing.
It's thejoiliest night we've ever had.

1174
00:41:36,884 --> 00:41:36,994


1175
00:41:36,995 --> 00:41:39,360
- Good night.
- Good night.

1176
00:41:39,361 --> 00:41:39,464


1177
00:41:39,464 --> 00:41:41,796
- Certainly a lovely party.
- What's this?

1178
00:41:41,796 --> 00:41:53,010


1179
00:41:53,011 --> 00:41:55,070
<i>[Speaking Indian Dialect]</i>

1180
00:41:55,070 --> 00:41:59,984


1181
00:41:59,984 --> 00:42:03,784
Chief Big Eagle say here bad Indians
who make trouble for covered wagon...

1182
00:42:03,784 --> 00:42:03,888


1183
00:42:03,888 --> 00:42:06,255
And steal horses
from Iron Horse camp.

1184
00:42:06,255 --> 00:42:06,356


1185
00:42:06,357 --> 00:42:10,123
He send to you.
Show redcoat he keep word.

1186
00:42:10,123 --> 00:42:15,366


1187
00:42:15,366 --> 00:42:18,165
Take them
to the guardroom.

1188
00:42:18,165 --> 00:42:36,320


1189
00:42:36,320 --> 00:42:39,119
- This fellow's dead, sir. He's been stabbed.
- They're all dead, sir.

1190
00:42:39,119 --> 00:42:46,263


1191
00:42:46,264 --> 00:42:48,494
Order out a detail
to bury them.

1192
00:42:48,494 --> 00:42:58,608


1193
00:42:58,609 --> 00:43:02,341
Well, this looks as if Big Eagle
is showing his defiance.

1194
00:43:02,341 --> 00:43:02,446


1195
00:43:02,447 --> 00:43:05,176
He knows the dispensing of justice
belongs to the Mounted Police.

1196
00:43:05,177 --> 00:43:05,283


1197
00:43:05,283 --> 00:43:08,615
I'll take that up with him
when he comes to sign the treaty.

1198
00:43:08,616 --> 00:43:08,719


1199
00:43:08,719 --> 00:43:11,416
If it's ever signed.

1200
00:43:11,416 --> 00:43:11,522


1201
00:43:11,522 --> 00:43:14,685
Chambers, if I should decide
to send Vicky home...

1202
00:43:14,685 --> 00:43:14,792


1203
00:43:14,792 --> 00:43:17,420
Could you do anything for me
in the way of transportation?

1204
00:43:17,420 --> 00:43:17,528


1205
00:43:17,528 --> 00:43:20,463
I certainly could, sir. There's a supply
train up on Sunday morning...

1206
00:43:20,464 --> 00:43:20,565


1207
00:43:20,565 --> 00:43:22,533
That'll take her as far
as Winnipeg.

1208
00:43:22,533 --> 00:43:22,633


1209
00:43:22,633 --> 00:43:24,795
From there, she can connect
with the Eastern Limited.

1210
00:43:24,795 --> 00:43:24,902


1211
00:43:24,902 --> 00:43:27,496
I agree with you. It'd be wise
to get her away from here.

1212
00:43:27,496 --> 00:43:27,605


1213
00:43:27,605 --> 00:43:30,336
- <i>I'll</i> let you know.
- No, thanks. I won't come in now.

1214
00:43:30,336 --> 00:43:30,440


1215
00:43:30,441 --> 00:43:33,433
I better get back to the camp
to see that everything's all right then.

1216
00:43:33,434 --> 00:43:33,543


1217
00:43:33,544 --> 00:43:35,740
- Good night.
- Good night, Chambers.

1218
00:43:35,740 --> 00:43:45,823


1219
00:43:45,823 --> 00:43:48,019
Won't you eat your eggs, sir?
They're that fresh...

1220
00:43:48,019 --> 00:43:48,125


1221
00:43:48,126 --> 00:43:51,458
I just saw the cook take them
from under the hen with his own hands.

1222
00:43:51,459 --> 00:43:51,562


1223
00:43:51,562 --> 00:43:53,587
Oh, no, thanks.

1224
00:43:53,588 --> 00:44:05,076


1225
00:44:05,076 --> 00:44:08,637
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

1226
00:44:08,637 --> 00:44:08,746


1227
00:44:08,746 --> 00:44:12,376
Here's your baked apple and milk.
All ready for you.

1228
00:44:12,376 --> 00:44:12,482


1229
00:44:12,483 --> 00:44:16,681
- I'm not hungry this morning, thank you.
- Heaven help us.

1230
00:44:16,682 --> 00:44:16,786


1231
00:44:16,787 --> 00:44:20,485
There's more than one sufferin' from the
same complaint this morning, I'm thinking.

1232
00:44:20,485 --> 00:44:20,591


1233
00:44:20,591 --> 00:44:22,559
Well, I'll get
a bit of work done. Sir?

1234
00:44:22,560 --> 00:44:22,660


1235
00:44:22,660 --> 00:44:24,958
Hmm? Oh, yes.
Go ahead.

1236
00:44:24,958 --> 00:44:31,435


1237
00:44:31,435 --> 00:44:33,403
Was it a nice party?

1238
00:44:33,404 --> 00:44:33,504


1239
00:44:33,504 --> 00:44:35,734
Yes, very nice.

1240
00:44:35,734 --> 00:44:35,840


1241
00:44:35,840 --> 00:44:37,865
Is she a good dancer?

1242
00:44:37,865 --> 00:44:37,975


1243
00:44:37,975 --> 00:44:40,740
Very good.

1244
00:44:40,740 --> 00:44:40,845


1245
00:44:40,845 --> 00:44:43,837
- Better than I am?
- No, I wouldn't say that.

1246
00:44:43,837 --> 00:44:46,183


1247
00:44:46,184 --> 00:44:48,708
- Are you going to marry her?
- Marry her?

1248
00:44:48,709 --> 00:44:48,819


1249
00:44:48,819 --> 00:44:53,347
Well, I was watching you
dance together last night.

1250
00:44:53,348 --> 00:44:53,456


1251
00:44:53,457 --> 00:44:57,519
And the way she looked at you, and the way
you looked at her, I thought maybe-

1252
00:44:57,519 --> 00:44:57,628


1253
00:44:57,628 --> 00:45:00,461
Don't you think you
ought to have your breakfast?

1254
00:45:00,461 --> 00:45:00,564


1255
00:45:00,565 --> 00:45:06,197
Yes, sir. But I supposed that when people
were in love, they always got married.

1256
00:45:06,197 --> 00:45:06,304


1257
00:45:06,304 --> 00:45:08,396
She's going home tomorrow.

1258
00:45:08,397 --> 00:45:08,506


1259
00:45:08,506 --> 00:45:10,598
Even Little Chief-

1260
00:45:10,599 --> 00:45:10,708


1261
00:45:10,708 --> 00:45:13,871
- She is? She's really going home?
- Mm-hmm.

1262
00:45:13,871 --> 00:45:13,978


1263
00:45:13,978 --> 00:45:17,414
Oh, isn't that a shame? Won't you sit
over here in the rocking chair?

1264
00:45:17,414 --> 00:45:17,515


1265
00:45:17,515 --> 00:45:19,916
- It's much more comfortable.
- No, thanks.

1266
00:45:19,916 --> 00:45:20,016


1267
00:45:20,017 --> 00:45:23,453
I'll get you your pipe.
Would you like your pipe?

1268
00:45:23,453 --> 00:45:23,554


1269
00:45:23,554 --> 00:45:26,649
Here's-
Here's some matches too.

1270
00:45:26,649 --> 00:45:26,757


1271
00:45:26,757 --> 00:45:31,558
I guess you smoke more matches than you do
tobacco. Can I get you anything else?

1272
00:45:31,559 --> 00:45:31,662


1273
00:45:31,662 --> 00:45:33,721
No, thanks. You'd better run along
and play with Little Chief.

1274
00:45:33,722 --> 00:45:33,831


1275
00:45:33,831 --> 00:45:36,994
- If you need me for anything,just send Mr. Pat.
- I will.

1276
00:45:36,994 --> 00:45:39,170


1277
00:45:39,170 --> 00:45:42,138
Hello, Mr. Pat!
Hello, Mr. Pat! Hello!

1278
00:45:42,139 --> 00:45:47,044


1279
00:45:47,044 --> 00:45:49,069
- Hello!
- Hello, Susannah.

1280
00:45:49,070 --> 00:45:55,952


1281
00:45:55,953 --> 00:45:59,389
<i>[ Men Chattering]</i>

1282
00:45:59,389 --> 00:46:16,106


1283
00:46:16,107 --> 00:46:18,371
- <i>Hi, Carruthers.</i>
- <i>[ Vicky] G000' morning.</i>

1284
00:46:18,371 --> 00:46:18,476


1285
00:46:18,476 --> 00:46:21,673
Oh, good morning, Miss Vicky.
I was hoping I'd see you before you left.

1286
00:46:21,673 --> 00:46:21,779


1287
00:46:21,779 --> 00:46:26,148
I'm sorry we have to say good-bye, but Dad
isn't in favor of my becoming a pioneer woman.

1288
00:46:26,148 --> 00:46:26,250


1289
00:46:26,250 --> 00:46:29,049
He's right, Miss Vicky.
This really isn't the place for you.

1290
00:46:29,049 --> 00:46:29,153


1291
00:46:29,153 --> 00:46:32,384
Are you going to keep it
a man's country forever?

1292
00:46:32,384 --> 00:46:32,489


1293
00:46:32,490 --> 00:46:34,720
It's apt to be that way
for quite a while yet.

1294
00:46:34,720 --> 00:46:34,824


1295
00:46:34,825 --> 00:46:38,557
Well, I suppose if we're ever to see each
other again, you'll have to come to Toronto.

1296
00:46:38,557 --> 00:46:38,662


1297
00:46:38,663 --> 00:46:40,857
I'm afraid there's not
much chance of that.

1298
00:46:40,858 --> 00:46:40,964


1299
00:46:40,965 --> 00:46:44,663
<i>- Why?
- We'll be pushing farther west every year...</i>

1300
00:46:44,663 --> 00:46:44,769


1301
00:46:44,769 --> 00:46:48,067
And by the time I get back to Toronto,
you'll probably be married...

1302
00:46:48,068 --> 00:46:48,172


1303
00:46:48,172 --> 00:46:50,834
<i>- And have a family of grown-up children.
- And what about you?</i>

1304
00:46:50,834 --> 00:46:50,941


1305
00:46:50,941 --> 00:46:55,242
Oh, I guess I'll just end up
being the old man of the mountain.

1306
00:46:55,242 --> 00:46:55,346


1307
00:46:55,346 --> 00:47:00,147
Well, good-bye.
I'll always remember the fun we've had...

1308
00:47:00,147 --> 00:47:00,250


1309
00:47:00,251 --> 00:47:04,085
And I'll probably find myself wishing I could
hear you sing that little waltz song again.

1310
00:47:04,085 --> 00:47:04,188


1311
00:47:04,188 --> 00:47:08,887
[Chuckles] And I'll find myself wishing
it wasn't so far to Toronto.

1312
00:47:08,887 --> 00:47:10,194


1313
00:47:10,194 --> 00:47:12,253
Good-bye, Vicky.

1314
00:47:12,253 --> 00:47:37,354


1315
00:47:37,355 --> 00:47:39,687
Squaw ride faster!

1316
00:47:39,687 --> 00:47:39,790


1317
00:47:39,790 --> 00:47:42,088
I'm coming
as fast as I can!

1318
00:47:42,089 --> 00:47:46,162


1319
00:47:46,163 --> 00:47:48,564
- Squaw ride like-
- Don't you dare say it!

1320
00:47:48,564 --> 00:47:48,666


1321
00:47:48,666 --> 00:47:51,964
- [Grunts]
- [ Chattering]

1322
00:47:51,965 --> 00:47:53,237


1323
00:47:53,237 --> 00:47:55,467
- White man buy?
- Take your time.

1324
00:47:55,467 --> 00:47:55,573


1325
00:47:55,573 --> 00:47:57,564
If they're sound,
we'll make a deal.

1326
00:47:57,564 --> 00:47:57,675


1327
00:47:57,675 --> 00:47:59,801
What are they doing
over there?

1328
00:47:59,802 --> 00:47:59,910


1329
00:47:59,910 --> 00:48:02,038
Wolf Pelt sell horses
to rail road.

1330
00:48:02,038 --> 00:48:02,146


1331
00:48:02,146 --> 00:48:04,308
Let's go watch.
Come on.

1332
00:48:04,308 --> 00:48:05,383


1333
00:48:05,383 --> 00:48:08,783
- [Grunts]
- Oh, all right!

1334
00:48:08,784 --> 00:48:08,886


1335
00:48:08,886 --> 00:48:12,789
Go ahead.
I'm getting used to being a squaw.

1336
00:48:12,789 --> 00:48:12,890


1337
00:48:12,890 --> 00:48:16,952
Aah! No have to look.
How much pay?

1338
00:48:16,952 --> 00:48:17,061


1339
00:48:17,061 --> 00:48:21,895
- <i>We '// settle that later.
- You'll buy now.</i> All good <i>horses.</i>

1340
00:48:21,896 --> 00:48:21,999


1341
00:48:21,999 --> 00:48:24,991
Sure. Three of them's very good horses.
They oughta be.

1342
00:48:24,991 --> 00:48:25,102


1343
00:48:25,102 --> 00:48:28,265
They're three that were stolen in the raid
and wasn't brought back with the others.

1344
00:48:28,265 --> 00:48:28,372


1345
00:48:28,372 --> 00:48:30,670
White man lie.
Indian ponies.

1346
00:48:30,670 --> 00:48:30,774


1347
00:48:30,775 --> 00:48:33,174
Yeah? Well,
there's Bully Boy...

1348
00:48:33,175 --> 00:48:33,277


1349
00:48:33,277 --> 00:48:36,076
That's Ladyjane,
and there's Steamboat.

1350
00:48:36,076 --> 00:48:36,180


1351
00:48:36,180 --> 00:48:38,205
And I'll prove it.

1352
00:48:38,205 --> 00:48:41,719


1353
00:48:41,719 --> 00:48:43,778
They didn't even make
a good job of dyeing it!

1354
00:48:43,778 --> 00:48:43,887


1355
00:48:43,888 --> 00:48:46,287
More of
your thieving tricks.

1356
00:48:46,288 --> 00:48:46,390


1357
00:48:46,390 --> 00:48:49,189
I wouldn't do business with your breed
if I had to go without horses!

1358
00:48:49,189 --> 00:48:49,293


1359
00:48:49,293 --> 00:48:51,284
You leave those animals here
and clear out.

1360
00:48:51,284 --> 00:48:51,395


1361
00:48:51,395 --> 00:48:54,330
- White man pay.
- <i>I'll</i> give you nothing.

1362
00:48:54,331 --> 00:48:54,432


1363
00:48:54,432 --> 00:48:56,797
<i>H' you got what you deserve,
I'd take it out of your hide!</i>

1364
00:48:56,798 --> 00:48:56,901


1365
00:48:56,901 --> 00:48:59,427
- Let us handle him, boss.
- We'll take care of him.

1366
00:48:59,427 --> 00:48:59,537


1367
00:48:59,537 --> 00:49:02,370
<i>- [Boss] Wait a minute! - You've been
babied by the redcoats long enough...</i>

1368
00:49:02,370 --> 00:49:02,473


1369
00:49:02,473 --> 00:49:04,532
But you're at the end
of the rope with me.

1370
00:49:04,532 --> 00:49:04,641


1371
00:49:04,642 --> 00:49:06,838
I'm going to have the rail road bring out
government troops to deal with you.

1372
00:49:06,838 --> 00:49:06,944


1373
00:49:06,944 --> 00:49:09,470
Iron Horse bring soldiers?

1374
00:49:09,470 --> 00:49:09,580


1375
00:49:09,580 --> 00:49:13,847
Yes, plenty of them.
They'll keep you in order... with bullets.

1376
00:49:13,847 --> 00:49:13,951


1377
00:49:13,951 --> 00:49:17,319
All right.
White chief has spoken.

1378
00:49:17,319 --> 00:49:17,421


1379
00:49:17,421 --> 00:49:19,890
- [Shouts In Indian Dialect]
- Don't let 'em get away!

1380
00:49:19,890 --> 00:49:19,990


1381
00:49:19,990 --> 00:49:22,220
[Men Shouting]

1382
00:49:22,220 --> 00:49:26,096


1383
00:49:26,096 --> 00:49:28,155
<i>[Shouting Continues]</i>

1384
00:49:28,156 --> 00:49:28,265


1385
00:49:28,265 --> 00:49:30,290
<i>[ Man]
Hold him up! Get him!</i>

1386
00:49:30,291 --> 00:49:32,837


